rComments: Prof Walker is very enthusiastic about the material and really engages her students. Lectures are 3 hour long though, which can get tiring. Weekly quizzes using TopHat which are not too hard, and tests and lecture based and fair. Assignments are graded very hard, put effort in them.
Clear expectations and is a good lecturer

rComments: I did not enjoy her lectures at all. They were incredibly boring and she would repeat the same concepts over and over for three hours. We never got out early, even though she promised us not all lectures would be the full three hours. I did not enjoy her teaching style and it's a shame since the content is so interesting.

She took over for Schimmack and thank god she did, she actually brought life to the material. She is bubbly and tries her best to ensure her students understand the material. I recommend taking this class with her or taking PSY290 with her.

Great proff. She engaes with the students a lot. Lectures and content is very interesting. Assignments are easy and graded expremely fair. Won't put everything on slides so make sure not to skip class.   MC can be tricky, SA is fair nothing surprising. Do the readings, go to the lectures and you'll be good

rComments: Really good lecturer. The only problem with this course is there is SO MUCH covered. Be prepared to memorize A LOT if you take this course. But her classes were good. Beware her tests, she is very specific, it's hard to do well on those!

Simone is a great lecturer. She goes through a lot of slides in the 3 hours so you can't depend on leaving early. She has a particular way of talking, but that never bothered me.  I had 3 classes with her this semester, and it was so difficult. Her assignments are crazy detailed, which is good. But that doesn't guarantee that you get a good mark.

rComments: I fell inlove with abnormal psych. She does use all 3h of the lecture but goes into great detail so I didn't read the textbook as much unless she asked to read over specific sections and you need it for the assignments so do purchase one. Lectures were interesting in my opinion and she's always available if help is needed.

Textbook is required and will show up as MC on tests and 1-2 smaller SA's. Lecture very heavy and theory content overload, so start studying early. The theory kind of makes even interesting course dry.  She goes the full 3 hours no matter # of slides (usually 50). MC on tests are half right type of tricky. Tests are mostly SA heavy. Tough grading.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: She's great at keeping your attention and you have to pay attention to her examples in detail, her stories etc. to succeed because it will all tie in. Look over past tests if you can. She is not the easiest lecturer for this course but not the hardest

Her division of the credit in this course was absurd, and the grading scheme for the assignments even more so. I absolutely hated the classes, long rambling lectures and sometimes would just literally summarize the textbook material, which sucked and was a waste of time.

She's very helpful if you ask for help. The tests are straight forward and right from the lectures but you have to know detailed answers (including the empirical studies that prove points). The two assignments have clear guidelines. Lastly, don't buy the textbook, it was a waste of $100,I didn't read a page of it and got a 90+ in her class.

Clear, concise, and to-the-point lectures. Everything on the tests are from the lectures (don't buy the textbook). She sometimes reuses old test questions, but don't count only on it. Her voice is weird at first, but you get used to it by the end. Very helpful, explains well, and replies to emails super fast. The best psych prof I've had!
really annoying high pitched voice. basically reads the slides to you, overlaps with majority of the textbook. class makes me fall asleep. m.c are hard, s-a ask for way too much detail to memorize.

To the point presentations and  no textbook required for class so tests are entirely based off lecture. Memorize the slides and an easy 80 is in your hands. Review past tests/exams for recycled questions.

Huge improvement from when I took her class before. The tests are all short answer, but in a way they are better then anything else. Marking seems fair, haven't had a problem. Only complaint - the way her voice rises and falls rocks me to sleep...

she's a great prof. VERY well spoken and to the point. Its easy to understand what she's talking about. The lecture slides are well put together. they're mini summaries of the textbook, so if you're a lazy student you dont have to read lol. tests were fair too, and on the exam 4/6 questions were repeated from past exam

Okay the textbook is really really important to do well in this course. On the plus side, you don't even need to go to lectures as long as you keep up with the textbook. She basically summarizes chapters in her lectures.

Even though lectures are just a summary of the textbook, She drops obvious HINTS for tests/exams during class. She gives very detailed test questions though. Went to her office hour she was really helpful!

Her lecture slides are basically a summary of what's in the textbooks. She even includes the same examples. In case of her speech, she's like a recording. Same tone throughout class and if she makes a mistake, she just keeps going on. In term of her tests, they're fair. She's just hard to listen to for 3 hours.
EXTREMELY HARD TESTS!!! shes a clear speaker.. but her tests are unreal!!!
